"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-culture-television-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-review-insane-cabaret-of-cliches-3193320\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  Europop, robohorse, boats, boats boats!\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 85, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This washed-out flotilla down the Seine was both deathly dull and totally mad, and I think I loved it  Oscillating between fist-eating dullness and unadulterated camp chaos, it's hard to know what to say about the Paris 2024 Olympics opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 86, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 120, \"end\": 125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.405674702043872e-18, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 306, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"2024 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Euro pop?\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 347, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Robo-horse?\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Naked blue man under cloche?\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, so many boats?\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watching brought up myriad complex emotions, none of them coherent - which, counterintuitively, put me in perfect step with this bonkers, boring show.\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What is there to compare an Olympic opening ceremony to?\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 616, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When else does a country cut together a four-hour long rendition of its own greatest hits, composed primarily of live acts that inevitably look terrible on television?\", \"from\": 617, \"to\": 784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Once every four years, that's when!\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I watched so you did not have to!\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first ceremony ever held outside a stadium, threading instead through the city via its legendary river Seine, Paris mixed up the usual format - fun performances first, interminable flag-trooping later - by interspersing the boring-but-necessary procession of athletes with its cabaret of national clich\\u00e9s.\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 1165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 970, \"end\": 975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.467071174241215e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That approach was a mixed bag - on the one hand, it was nice to have the seemingly endless flotilla of national boats carrying athletes interrupted every now and then.\", \"from\": 1167, \"to\": 1334, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the other, it drew out the boat thing for what felt like several years; even the pleasure of saying \\\"ha!\\\"\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"about geographically unlikely pairings, thrown together in French alphabetical order, had worn off by the time we got to Central African Republic and Canada, let alone Portugal and Qatar.\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1503, \"end\": 1509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9783871432626824, \"rank\": 0.02206152183451631, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1565, \"end\": 1589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_African_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9999992639325663, \"rank\": 7.360681619039769e-07, \"text\": \"Central African Republic\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_African_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_African_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 1594, \"end\": 1600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999982624104, \"rank\": 1.5155417203154465e-09, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\", \"score\": 0.992873523711974, \"rank\": 0.006996157423137566, \"text\": \"Portugal\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\"}, {\"begin\": 1625, \"end\": 1630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"score\": 0.9999700551975103, \"rank\": 2.994569913133909e-05, \"text\": \"Qatar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qatar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, there was a lot of pressure on the cut-away performances to keep us entertained.\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We started strong with Lady Gaga, who delivered a delightful rendition of \\\"Mon Truc en Plumes\\\"by Zizi Jeanmaire, dressed in black and flanked by dancers wafting pink feather pom poms.\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1746, \"end\": 1755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 1820, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zizi Jeanmaire\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Jeanmaire\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the Olympic torch was carried through the city by a mysterious hooded figure, who took helpful detours through iconic buildings and indulged in a spot of parkour on the city's picturesque roofs; cutting between sunny pre-filmed and gloomy live footage only underscored the (largely outdoors) ceremony's miserable weather, where rain was sometimes heavy enough to be audible on the TV: literally raining on Paris's parade.\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 2340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2325, \"end\": 2330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.467071174241215e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But - to chuck another clich\\u00e9 in the mix - the show had to go on.\", \"from\": 2342, \"to\": 2407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfazed by the weather (let alone today's travel chaos), things valiantly got weirder and weirder.\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Metal band Gojira were accompanied by headless Marie Antoinette and flame throwers; three eccentrically dressed students in a library hooked up for an inexplicablem\\u00e9nage a trois; there was a whole skit with Minions and theMona Lisa; people in Louis XIV get-up did BMX tricks.\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2782, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2518, \"end\": 2524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2718813272989107e-35, \"text\": \"Gojira\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godzilla\"}, {\"begin\": 2554, \"end\": 2570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4129265647461785e-29, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}, {\"begin\": 2734, \"end\": 2738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Simpson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.216838904936131e-23, \"text\": \"Lisa\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Simpson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Simpson\"}, {\"begin\": 2750, \"end\": 2759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"score\": 0.9999999955393832, \"rank\": 4.460436724449192e-09, \"text\": \"Louis XIV\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\"}, {\"begin\": 2771, \"end\": 2774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999832519731229, \"rank\": 1.6748301880714843e-05, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure, some less strange stuff happened - a performance by Aya Nakamura, the most listened-to female French language singer on Spotify, was a triumph - but by this point the madness was all that was keeping me going.\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2842, \"end\": 2854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}, {\"begin\": 2910, \"end\": 2917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Spotify\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spotify\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Luckily, musician Phillipe Katerine was hiding under a cloche, painted blue and singing about being naked, so I did not have to go without for long.\", \"from\": 3000, \"to\": 3148, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Euro-pop medley helped, too, thanks for asking.\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3153, \"end\": 3161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Europop\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Euro-pop\", \"types\": [\"Q188451\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Europop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Europop\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a few forays into earnestness - someone sang \\\"Imagine\\\"next to a burning piano; 10 statues of influential French women rose out of the water like zombies - the ceremony managed to pinball between insanity and deathly dullness with very little in-between.\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3315, \"end\": 3321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9783871432626824, \"rank\": 0.02206152183451631, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was as if a different person - no, a different species - had conceived of each individual part, and they'd met to discuss it 20 minutes before kick-off; I am not complaining, just processing.\", \"from\": 3464, \"to\": 3658, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If we must do these ceremonies, you could do much worse than Paris's model - but, must we?\", \"from\": 3659, \"to\": 3749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3720, \"end\": 3725, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.467071174241215e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In its fourth hour, and as the spectacle gave way to speeches, my poor brain could finally stop whirring like an overheating processor.\", \"from\": 3751, \"to\": 3886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not even C\\u00e9line Dion singing in the Eiffel Tower, as she did for the grand finale, could rouse me; there was no sense to be made, no dots to join, I have used up my attention span for the next four years.\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 4091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris, je t'aime; see you in Los Angeles in 2028.\", \"from\": 4092, \"to\": 4141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4092, \"end\": 4108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris,_je_t'aime\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris, je t'aime\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris,_je_t'aime\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris,_je_t'aime\"}, {\"begin\": 4121, \"end\": 4132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2272476200629066e-19, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate  All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 4143, \"to\": 4200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Associated Newspapers Limited.\", \"from\": 4201, \"to\": 4238, \"entities\": []}]}"